.TH creat 2 "25 Mar 2002" "SunOS 5.11" "System Calls"
.SH NAME
creat \- create a new file or rewrite an existing one
.SH SYNOPSIS
.LP
.nf
#include <sys/stat.h>
#include <fcntl.h>

\fBint\fR \fBcreat\fR(\fBconst char *\fIpath\fR, \fBmode_t\fR \fImode\fR);
.fi

.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
.LP
The function call
.sp
.LP
creat(path, mode)
.sp
.LP
is equivalent to:
.sp
.LP
.B "open(path, O_WRONLY | O_CREAT | O_TRUNC, mode)
.SH RETURN VALUES
.sp
.LP
Refer to
.BR open (2).
.SH ERRORS
.sp
.LP
Refer to
.BR open (2).
.SH EXAMPLES
.LP
.B Example 1
Creating a File
.sp
.LP
The following example creates the file
.B /tmp/file
with read and write
permissions for the file owner and read permission for group and others. The
resulting file descriptor is assigned to the
.I fd
variable.

.sp
.in +2
.nf
#include <fcntl.h>
\&...
int fd;
mode_t mode = S_IRUSR | S_IWUSR | S_IRGRP | S_IROTH;
char *filename = "/tmp/file";
\&...
fd = creat(filename, mode);
\&...
.fi
.in -2

.SH USAGE
.sp
.LP
The
.B creat()
function has a transitional interface for 64-bit file
offsets. See
.BR lf64 (5).
